value.value: Formation of the intercellular bridges that connect the germ-line cells of a male cyst.

Formation, in a germarium, of a group of interconnected cells derived from a single female gonial founder cell (a cystoblast). The germarium is the most anterior portion of an insect ovariole. An example of this process is found in Drosophila melanogaster.
The release of a mature ovum/oocyte from an ovary.

definition.value: This term may be used to annotate both partners in a GTP-dependent binding interaction, both the GTP-bound protein and the protein(s) which interact with it.
